main event: A round pink object, the size of a basketball held at arms length, was observed at an altitude of one to two thousand feet in Waupun, Wisconsin on June 6, 1956.
interesting points: The object was still in sight at the time of the report.
The sighting occurred in accordance with Air Force Regulation 80-24.
The witness, Howard Teschner, was 47 years old.
The object was observed for 5 minutes from 0311 to 0316 hours.
No further details about the sighting were provided.
